nodes.bodyText:
For readability I'd turn these if's order and avoid the boolean hasAFilter:
if (indexOfFirstFilter >= 0) {
      if (joiner instanceof FilteringBiJoiner) {
        throw ...
      }
} else if (joiner instanceof FilteringBiJoiner) {
    indexOfFirstFilter = i;
}

Most of OptaPlanner's code has the style to first check the fail fasts, before doing the code. I've found this is more readable, because when reading you can skip the fail-fasts, reducing the lines to grok (fail-fast's are usually easy to recognize based on their "throw" keyword).

